CATEGORY=FEAT|Bloodthirsty.MOD				DESC:After a daylong ritual involving the caster and at least six others, one of whom must be a necromancer, the caster gains master of the blood. If a Bloodleech spell has been cast in the last 24 hours normal healing is at an accelerated rate, recovering hit points equal to twice character level with a night of rest, or three times character level with an entire day and night of rest.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Elemalefic Spellcaster.MOD	DESC:After a daylong ritual involving an invocation to angry elemental spirits, the caster can call up their rage to enhance spells. The caster gains a +2 bonus to Survival checks made while on any of the four elemental planes.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Ethereal Tendril.MOD			DESC:A daylong ceremony in which the caster sacrifices and devours an ether scarab. The caster gains the ability to move at normal speed (instead of half speed) when traveling on the Ethereal Plane.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Invigorating Spellcaster.MOD	DESC:A daylong ritual involving the caster and six clerics, the caster gains a +2 bonus on all Heal checks.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Spellbinder.MOD				DESC:A daylong ritual during which the caster and six participants are shackled together at the ankles, the caster gains a +2 bonus on Use Rope checks made to bind a creature. 
CATEGORY=FEAT|Spellstrike.MOD				DESC:After a daylong ritual involving the caster and at least six monks, the caster gains a +2 bonus to Concentration checks made to ignore vigorous, violent, or extraordinary violent motion while casting spells. 
CATEGORY=FEAT|Superior Summons.MOD			DESC:After a daylong ritual involving the caster and six others, at least one of whom is a conjurer, the caster gains a +1 bonus to caster level for Conjuration (Summoning) spells. 


