CATEGORY=FEAT|Bloodleech.MOD	DESC:A Bloodleech spell is considered an evil act deals an additional 1d6 damage to a living creature that is transfer to the caster as healing. Required verbal components which cannot be modified and a 25gp ruby.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Champion.MOD		DESC:Champion spell summoned creatures have maximum hit points and can receive touch spells from the caster at line of sight. Requires a 250gp topaz as an additional material component.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Concussive.MOD	DESC:An creature hit by a Concussive spell must make a Balance check (DC 10 + caster level) or be knocked prone. Requires somatic components that cannot be modified and a 25gp pearl.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Ghost Touch.MOD	DESC:Ghost Touch spells gain the Ghost Touch weapon property and are not subject to the 50% miss chance normally applied to incorporeal targets. Requires a 50gp silver orb.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Elemalefic.MOD	DESC:This spell template can be added to any spell that does energy damage. Elemental spirits continue to deal typed damage to spell targets, 1d4, for a number of rounds equal to the spell level. Required material component costs 50gp and is specific to energy type: black dragon drool (acid), diamond dust (cold), star made of woven coper (electricity), ruby dust (fire), golden tuning fork (sonic).
CATEGORY=FEAT|Invigorating.MOD	DESC:This spell template can be added to any spell that heals hit points. In addition to healing damage it also removes the following conditions affects: dazed, exhausted, fatigued, sickened, and stunned. Required verbal component which cannot be modified.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Shackled.MOD		DESC:This spell template can be added to any spell with a duration other than instantaneous or permanent. Targets of a Shackled spell move at one-half its normal spell (rounded to the next 5-foot increment) for the duration of the spell. Required somatic components that cannot be modified. Requires a material focus (set of silver shackles worth at least 100gp) and a material component (a golden key worth at least 25gp). This templates cannot be applied to 9th level spells.

